The Telegraph - Calcutta
 Monday, October 21, 2002  Calcutta Column
				 																																									Flyovers coming up at several points in the city are inconveniencing commuters. Moreover, the gas cylinders used for sawing iron and steel grids are very expensive and risky if left exposed. The cylinders should be shifted elsewhere. 				 																																									Sumant Poddar,				 																																									Kyd Street.				 																																									The Howrah Municipal Corporation had installed traffic signals at the Salkia-Chowrasta intersection at least twice in the past year. But some miscreants broke the light posts within a few days. If the authorities plan to reinstal the signals, they should ensure that the lights are covered with iron nets. Signals need to be installed at the earliest.				 																																									B.L. Chandak,				 																																									Salkia.
